    sections: [
      { heading: "Who uses them, and for what", body: "On a production the fleet serves every department in turn. Transport and ADs move cast and crew between unit base, set and location, and the AD team uses them to cover ground fast on a sprawling site. Grips, sparks and props move equipment, cable and dressing across a location quietly, and the same vehicles keep a noise-sensitive set running between takes." },
      { heading: "Recommended models and fleet make-up", body: "The Eight is a true unit shuttle for cast and crew, with The Six suited to smaller units and rapid moves. The Utility handles equipment and kit across a location, and a Bespoke build covers picture vehicles and engineered conversions. A production typically takes a mixed fleet for the dates, passenger carriages from £18,900 for the six-seat and £23,500 for the eight-seat, plus utilities and bespoke vehicles to brief." },
      { heading: "Picture vehicles, branding and conversions", body: "Bespoke commissions are a core service for film and television, delivering period liveries, branded set dressing and engineered conversions to a production's exact brief. Standard fleet vehicles can equally be wrapped or finished through the Branding step for a unit's identity or a sponsor. From a vehicle that appears in shot to one dressed for a base camp, we build to the production design rather than from a catalogue." },
      { heading: "Range, charging and a shoot day", body: "Shoot days are long and unpredictable, so lithium batteries are specified for sustained stop-start running across a full day, and we plan charging at unit base so the fleet is ready for an early call. Charging points and a routine are agreed for the location, and across a larger fleet charging is staggered so cover holds through overruns. Fast-charge options are discussed where a shoot runs into the night." },
      { heading: "Silent on location and on noise-sensitive sites", body: "Near-silent electric drivetrains keep vehicles usable during takes and on noise-sensitive locations where a petrol engine cannot run, which is the core reason productions choose electric. Zero fumes also matter on heritage interiors and protected natural sites where air quality is a condition of access. The fleet moves people and kit between setups without the sound department calling cut." },
      { heading: "Where they can be driven, supply and support", body: "Standard vehicles are built for the location and unit base, private land, which is where the work happens. Where a route uses a public road, only a genuinely type-approved, road-legal specification is road legal, and we advise honestly on what that requires. Productions usually take vehicles for the dates, every build carries a 3-year warranty and a 24-hour VIP call-out, and as a British marque we aim to beat any genuine like-for-like quote." },
    ],
    useCases: ["Cast and crew unit transport", "AD rapid movement across location", "Equipment, cable and dressing moves", "Bespoke picture vehicles in shot", "Period and branded set-dressing conversions", "Silent running on noise-sensitive sets", "Zero-fume access to heritage interiors", "Base-camp and catering logistics"],
