    metaDescription: "Custom-made electric buggies for theme parks and amusement parks worldwide, from the Middle East to the US. Branded medical, grounds, staff, VIP and accessible PRM fleets, made to order in Britain.",
    intro: "A theme park is a small city that runs on movement. From first-aid teams reaching a guest in minutes to grounds crews servicing rides before the gates open, executive hosts escorting partners, and families who need an accessible way around the site, everything depends on quiet, dependable electric vehicles. We build custom-made theme park buggies to order in Britain and deliver them worldwide, from the Middle East to the United States, each one branded to the park and specified for the exact job it has to do.",
    problem: "A theme park has to move people and equipment constantly across a large, crowded site, all day and often late into the night, while keeping the experience immersive. Petrol vehicles bring noise, fumes and fuel handling that break the spell and sit badly in pedestrian-heavy areas, and a generic cart looks wrong against a carefully themed park. At the same time the operation has very different transport needs at once: emergency medical response, grounds and maintenance, staff shuttles, executive and VIP hosting, and accessible transport for guests with reduced mobility. The challenge is one fleet that covers all of it, cleanly, quietly and on brand.",
    sections: [
      { heading: "Custom-made for every role in the park", body: "No two park vehicles do the same job, so none are built the same way. We make medical and first-aid response buggies with space for a stretcher, equipment and a response crew; grounds and maintenance vehicles with a load bed for tools, parts and waste; staff and crew shuttles to move teams between zones at shift change; executive carriages for hosting partners, sponsors and press; and custom VIP buggies for private groups and front-of-line guest experiences. Whatever the need, we design the vehicle around it rather than adapting a generic cart." },
      { heading: "Medical and emergency response", body: "When a guest needs help, minutes matter. A purpose-built first-aid buggy carries your medical team, a stretcher or carry-chair, oxygen and response kit directly to the incident through crowds where an ambulance cannot go, then moves the patient to your medical centre or a waiting ambulance. Silent electric running means no engine noise around a casualty, and the layout, lighting and equipment mounts are specified with your medical lead so the vehicle works the way your team does." },
      { heading: "Branded fleets and custom-made solutions", body: "Every vehicle is a bespoke build finished to the park. Liveries are matched to park colours and land themes, characters and logos are applied through the Branding step of the configurator and confirmed at quotation, and individual zones can run their own livery so a vehicle reads as part of the scene. Custom-made solutions extend to bodywork, seating layout, signage, lighting and equipment fit-out, so a medical buggy, a grounds vehicle and a VIP carriage can share a fleet identity while each does its own job." },
      { heading: "Accessibility and PRM guest transport", body: "Large parks are tiring to cross, and not every guest can manage the distances. We supply wheelchair-accessible, ramp-equipped vehicles with assisted boarding so guests with reduced mobility, older visitors and families with young children can move around the park comfortably and with dignity. An accessible guest-transport service is both a genuine kindness and a practical way to keep your whole site welcoming, and we specify the vehicles so your team can run them easily every day." },
      { heading: "Capacity, range and all-day, late-night running", body: "Park days are long and often run into the evening, so lithium batteries are specified for constant stop-start use across opening hours and night events on a single overnight charge. We plan charging points and a charging routine, and stagger charging across a larger fleet, so medical, grounds and guest vehicles are always available rather than waiting on a socket. Where a park runs near-continuous operations we discuss fast-charge and spare-battery options at the survey." },
      { heading: "Worldwide delivery, servicing and uptime", body: "We deliver and support theme parks worldwide, from Gulf resort parks to US destinations, with vehicles built to order in Britain and shipped to site. Every build carries a 3-year warranty and a 24-hour VIP call-out, and for international operators our experts aim to reach you within 24 to 48 hours so a vehicle is never long out of action during opening season. Electric drivetrains need far less maintenance than petrol, and as a British marque we aim to beat any genuine like-for-like quote." },
    ],
    useCases: ["Medical and first-aid emergency response", "Wheelchair-accessible PRM guest transport", "Grounds, rides and maintenance crews", "Staff and crew shuttles between zones", "Executive hosting for partners and sponsors", "Custom VIP buggies for private groups", "Front-of-line and premium guest experiences", "Night events, parades and after-hours operations"],
